text.tspan: private Map<Integer, String> nodes
, this attribute is a HashMap, composed by an Integer
key and a String value. The values of this attribute
represent nodes to be inserted in the
graph: the key is the id of the node, while the value
is the name of the node. The HashMap
allows fast access based on the id.
private Map<Integer[], String> edges
, this attribute
is a HashMap, composed by an array of
Integers for the key and a String value. The values
of this attribute represent the edges that
connect nodes in the graph: the key is an array of
the ids of the nodes it connects, while the
value is the name of the arc.
private Map<String, Integer> wikiMatches
, this attribute
is a HashMap, composed by a
String key and a Integer value. This Map stores matches
for an entity found in a Wikipedia
search. The string is the name of the entity, while
the Integer is the id of the corresponding
Wikipedia page. This attribute is used to optimize
searches, storing already known values,
not having to look up Wikipedia multiple times.
private List<String> removePronouns
, this attribute
is an ArrayList of Strings, that stores
known pronouns, that we do not want to insert into
the nodes Map. To do this we simply
check if the node’s name is in the List.

public void addRelation(String s, String r, String
o)
, this is the main method of the class; it
takes in input a triple, composed by three strings
that represent the subject, relation and
object respectively.
First if the subject or the object of the triple are
a pronoun contained in the attribute
removePronouns, it returns (this is done to avoid
having connections in the graph that are
referred to an unknown entity).
Then if the node Map attribute is empty it automatically
adds a node for the subject and
object and an edge which connects them; the ids for
the nodes are generated by hashing the
name of the nodes (only positive integer). This ids,
obtained with hashing, are needed in
order to optimize the search for duplicates.
If not empty, the method checks for aliases, already
inserted in the nodes Map, by cycling
through and confronting the current node with the
nodes to be inserted (both for subject
and object). If a match is found, the node is added,
but a new edge (for the alias relationship)
is inserted between the matched nodes. If the match
is not found, it simply adds the nodes
to the Map and at the end inserts an edge for the
relationship specified in the input.
private boolean matchPageId(String s1, String s2)
this method performs the searches on
Wikipedia to return true, if the two Strings in input
match the same Wiki Page, false
otherwise. To do this in an optimized way, it uses
the attribute WikiMatches to check if a
search has already performed for that specific String;
if not, it performs the search (this is
delegated to the WikipediaIntegration Class), and
adds the result to the Map.
public void printEdges()
, this method prints all the
edges currently inserted. It is only used
for debugging purposes.
